Files:
- plugins/tiktok/src/tiktok-api.ts (lines 149-159, the api() function response handling)

Context:
Current code (lines 149-159):
  if (response.status === 200) {
    const text = await response.text();
    if (text.length === 0) {
      throw ToolError.internal('TikTok returned an empty response...');
    }
    return JSON.parse(text) as T;
  }

  // fetchFromPage already throws on non-ok; this is a fallback
  const text = await response.text();
  throw ToolError.internal(`TikTok API error: ${response.status} ${text.substring(0, 200)}`);

Since fetchFromPage throws on non-ok, the else branch is only reached for 201/202/204. The fix:
  if (response.status === 204) return {} as T; // No Content
  const text = await response.text();
  if (text.length === 0) {
    throw ToolError.internal('TikTok returned an empty response — the endpoint may require additional signing.');
  }
  return JSON.parse(text) as T;

Remove the entire dead fallback block (lines 157-159).

Constraints:
- The empty-response ToolError message must remain exactly as is
- The JSON.parse wrapping is intentional (TikTok returns plain text JSON, not streams)
- Do NOT change the signing logic or URL construction above line 149
